== japanese-menu.el ==

Translate Emacs GUI menus (menu-bar, pull-down menus, popup menus)
from English to Japanese using a label dictionary.

This package targets GNU Emacs GUI on Debian / Ubuntu systems.

=== Features ===
* Translates menu-bar labels
* Translates pull-down menus
* Translates mode-specific menus (e.g. Info-mode)
* Translates popup menus (right-click)

=== Installation ===
1. Put japanese-menu.el somewhere in your load-path, e.g.:

 ~/.emacs.d/lisp/japanese-menu.el

2. Add to your init.el:

 (add-to-list 'load-path "~/.emacs.d/lisp")
 (require 'japanese-menu)
 (japanese-menu-setup)

=== Usage ===
Restart Emacs or evaluate init.el.
You can also manually run:

 M-x japanese-menu-translate-current-menubar

=== Verified Environment ===
* Host OS: macOS (VMware Fusion)
* Guest OS: Ubuntu (aarch64)
* Desktop: GNOME (Wayland)
* Emacs: GNU Emacs 30.1 (GTK)

=== Download ===
Download
GitHub Releases:
https://github.com/yt-emacs-ja/emacs-japanese-menu/releases




=== Notes ===
* This package is for GUI Emacs only.
* Terminal Emacs (emacs -nw) is not supported.
* Menu labels may vary depending on Emacs version and packages.

